Hence sprang the art of medicine. Such things alone had Nature decreed should be our remedies, pro- vided everywhere, easy to discover and costing noth- ing—the things in fact that support our life. Later on the deceit of men and cunning profiteering led to the invention of the quack laboratories, in which each customer is promised a new lease of his own life at a price.
